<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[198,780,191,218]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,549,191,217]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis. Imago (external).</emphasis>
Wingspan: 
<quantity box="[690,776,192,218]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Head, patagia, anterior part of tegulae, prothorax, basal part of costa, triangular patch of medial area, and terminal area, including fringes: black.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[197,954,312,338]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Forewing ground colour: beige suffused with light brown scales.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[197,851,352,378]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Abdomen: dark grey; with dorsal tuft on basal segment.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[197,1423,392,418]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Crosslines: untraceable, except weak antemedial line and terminal line marked by black interneural dots.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[197,744,432,458]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Reniform stigma: beige, ovoid, black outlined.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[197,1254,472,498]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Hindwing: beige; with narrow brown terminal line; fringes white basally, otherwise beige.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[197,770,512,538]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Underside: forewing grey brown, hindwing grey.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[198,1149,551,578]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,384,551,577]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Tegumen: long, laterally narrow, dorso-laterally broad, platelike.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[197,1158,592,618]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Vinculum: two branched; centre one barlike; posterior one branchlike, not curved.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[197,582,632,658]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Saccus: short; broadly V shaped.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[197,1250,672,698]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Valvae: asymmetrical; subapically with prominent, triangular, broad-based process (apo.).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Ampulla: slightly asymmetrical; similar to head of ‘Snoopy’ (cartoon dog); tapered towards dorsal tip (apo.).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[197,684,792,818]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Digitus: small, triangular, apically setose.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Anellus plate: prominently asymmetrical; with very long, free, medially curved, heavily sclerotised clublike structure; head of club clothed with stout setae (apo.).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[197,774,912,938]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Juxta: trapezoid, with medial cleft on dorsal side.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
Phallus: coecum short and very broad; broadest by ductus ejaculatorius; smoothly and upwards strongly curved 80 
<superScript attach="left" box="[267,275,992,1006]" fontSize="6" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">o</superScript>
to pointed tip (apo.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[197,399,1034,1060]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Vesica: unarmed.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[198,1024,1074,1100]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,473,1074,1100]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[480,600,1075,1100]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Fustis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sensora">
<emphasis box="[480,600,1075,1100]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">F. sensora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other 
<taxonomicName box="[822,986,1074,1100]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Fustis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[822,893,1075,1100]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fustis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[198,657,1114,1140]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">- narrow wings, with pointed apex;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[198,951,1154,1180]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">- beige-brown ground colour, with contrasting wing pattern;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[198,400,1194,1220]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">male genitalia, in</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[198,1087,1234,1260]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">- shape of ampulla, ventral broad, rounded end, and dorsal pointed arm;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[198,858,1274,1300]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">- very large, medially curved, brushlike anellus; and</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,152,1380]" box="[198,612,1314,1340]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">- long, curved, tapered phallus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
